  'clock was most fashionable during the 18th century, though few were adorned with tortoiseshell, '
  'a costly decorative accent reserved for only the finest pieces. The bronze mounts of floral '
  'sprays, scrolls, and garlands are among the most elaborate created for a bracket clock. Retains '
  'its original matching wall bracket. Enamel dial signed, "Chiout L\'Aine, Paris 1749." The '
  'production of magnificent bracket clocks flourished in France during the 18th and 19th '
  'centuries due to royal and aristocratic patronage. French clocks, considered merely a '
  'decorative object, proved to be far more ornate than their English counterparts. Eighteenth '
