  'The musician catapulted from star to legend when he adopted the unpronounceable glyph as his '
  'stage name in 1993, partially in defiance of his record label, Warner Bros. A blend of the '
  "ancient symbols of man and woman, it has since come to represent not only the artist's fluid "
  'sexuality, but also the triumph of harmony over conflict. After he adopted the "Love Symbol," '
