  'beautifully carved in this Black Forest inkwell and pen stand. The jovial ursine figure is '
  'reaching into the hollowed out log as if for a snack. The incredible artistry of the Swiss '
  'Black Forest wood carvers is on display in this charming form, with its wide brown glass eyes, '
  'exquisitely detailed coat, and lovely patina. The wood carving industry of Switzerland emerged '
  'in the early 19th century, and Swiss Black Forest carvings quickly became world renowned for '
  'their quality and craftsmanship. Black Forest carvings were spotlighted at a number of '
  'international exhibitions, including the Great Exhibition in London in 1851, the Chicago '
  "World's Fair in 1893 and the Exposition Universelle in Paris in 1900, and these delightful "
