  'purples, and violets, Blue John was in great demand during the 18th and early 19th centuries. '
  'The colorful and decorative stone was even worked into columns in some of the finest houses in '
  'Great Britain, most notably Chatsworth, home of the Duchess of Devonshire. The name ‘Blue John’ '
  'is thought to originate from the French term bleu et jaune, meaning blue and yellow. The '
