  'of vibrant color, from soft yellows to cool blues and violets that form the silhouette of the '
  "lamp's foliate motif. Gallé was renowned for his naturalistic glass artistry, and today he is "
  'considered one of the pioneers of the Art Nouveau style. Uncertain about the staying power of '
  'electricity at the turn of the century, he produced relatively few of these lamps, making '
  'surviving examples such as this quite scarce. Unique hand-crafted lamps such as this are '
