  'European affairs in the years following the French Revolution. Colombo depicts the leader in '
  'his familiar military garb, celebrating Napoleon’s legendary life and lasting accomplishments. '
  'Below the emperor rests an eagle clutching a double-ended torch, a classic symbol of honor and '
  'courage. The eagle was a symbol chosen by Napoleon himself as an emblem of the new era in '
