  'cultural tradition of adornment, utilizing some of the most advanced gold-casting techniques '
  'known to the world at that time. This necklace was likely made for an elite individual, such as '
  'a priest or a high-ranking official, as part of their adornment collection. Both men and women '
  'would wear up to 60 lbs of gold in the form of breastplates, pendants and rings, symbolizing '
  'their rank and prestige. This necklace was among the many gold ornaments found along ancient '
