  '16th century through the early 19th century, glassware from Nevers was highly prized and has '
  'often been mistaken for fine porcelain. The glass-making tradition was originally brought to '
  "the city by Italian settlers from L'Altare. Known as Altarists, these glassmakers were expert "
  'craftsmen of crystal and colored glass. Their skills were mainly utilized in the production of '
