  'the American cultural landscape as Frank Sinatra. A true Renaissance man, Sinatra was not only '
  'a talented singer and actor, but also a painter of great skill. This oil on canvas is a vibrant '
  'example of the abstract compositions that he created during his later years in the 1980s. Like '
  'many of his works, it pays homage to the American legacy of abstraction, highlighting color and '
  'form while leaving subject behind. For most of his life, Sinatra was an art lover. After rising '
  'to fame, he also became a collector of significance, acquiring works by artists such as Pablo '
