  'outstanding work of English cabinetmaking. The name of Thomas Chippendale is most closely '
  'associated with English Rococo-style furniture. More than a simple cabinetmaker, he was an '
  'innovator and visionary. His name has become synonymous with a distinguishable style not '
  'because the furniture was made by him or his factory, but because of his foresight in '
  'publishing his incredible designs. In 1754, he published the first of three editions of The '
