  '1369-1415). The foremost of the Czech reformers, Huss served as a professor of philosophy and '
  'rector of the Charles University in Prague. He was responsible for leading a movement against '
  'doctrinal positions of the Roman Catholic church which resulted in Huss being labeled as a '
  'heretic. In 1414, a long trial began at the Council of Constance and on July 6, 1415 Huss was '
  'burned at the stake for his heresy. Huss is remembered for fostering the reformation spirit in '
  'Bohemia, which eventually led to the organization of the modern day Moravian Church. Porcelain '
  'impressed with Berlin eagle mark and KPM cyphers. Excellent condition. Signed and dated O. '
