  'turquoise-blue enamel thumbpiece adds a touch of refinement to the luxurious design. The case '
  'bears the 84 zolotniks mark of St. Petersburg, along with the assayer’s mark of Yakova '
  'Ljapunova and a partial silversmith’s mark. Unlike paint, enamel is a thin layer of glass '
  "expertly applied to metal. When heated, the glass melts and fuses to the metal's surface, "
  'creating a durable, glossy finish. Pairing enamel with metals like gold, silver, or copper '
