  'President of the United States, James Madison. Initially issued to help finance the American '
  'Revolutionary War, the first official $5,000 Federal notes were printed during the Civil War. '
  'Last printed in 1945 and officially discontinued in 1969, today these bills are exceptional '
  'rarities. Large-denomination currency first emerged in the United States in the late 18th '
  'century, with the first $500 note being issued in North Carolina in 1780. They generally '
