  'important men to wear gold jewels on their chests, head, and arms during battle. The gold would '
  'immediately differentiate the chief to both his men, and to his enemies. These pectoral discs, '
  'therefore, were worn as symbols of high status and prestige, reserved for the most elite of the '
  'Diquís region. The Diquís culture arose in the territory of what is now Costa Rica, along the '
