  'young girl holding a precious pearl necklace beside a shallow pool of green veined marble. '
  'Comprised of carved ivory and cast, gilded bronze in a medium known as chryselephantine, this '
  'ethereal figure is both classical and evocative. Johann Philipp Ferdinand Preiss (1882-1943) is '
  'widely considered to be one of the most important ivory carvers of the Art Deco era. His work '
  'embodies the exuberance and stylish ideals of the Jazz Age. Filled with kinetic energy, these '
  'models are filled with the new sense of freedom and confidence that this era ushered in. His '
