  'this bronze bust captures the American Founding Father George Washington, as rendered by '
  'Italian-American artist Antonio Bianchini. Finely detailed depictions such as this were '
  "remarkably popular both during and after Washington's lifetime, when the President's iconic "
  'persona became a cornerstone of American national identity. Images of Washington as a general '
  'were favored as depictions of the President in his uniform came to symbolize the military '
  "victories of the United States, as well as the country's continued liberty and unity. Antonio "
  'Bianchini designed this monumental bronze for the renowned Gorham & Co., founded by Jabez '
  'Gotham of Providence, Rhode Island in 1831. The firm initially began by manufacturing '
