  'Celebrated for its unique bands of blues, purples, and violets, Blue John was in great demand '
  'during the 18th and early 19th centuries. The colorful and decorative stone was even worked '
  'into columns in some of the finest houses in Great Britain, most notably Chatsworth, home of '
