  'The casket was part of the Second Renaissance Revival that swept through France from 1890 until '
  '1915, which saw a renewed interest in classical motifs borrowed from Greek, Roman and Egyptian '
  'art and architecture. Due to the expense of the materials and high level of craftsmanship '
  'necessary to execute this elaborate design style, the Renaissance Revival craze was almost '
  'solely reserved for the grand homes of the very wealthy. This specimen casket reflects the '
  'grandeur of the age. Its architectural silvered and gilt bronze form is adorned by pierced '
