  'also detachable. Engraved with a coat-of-arms and crest. Beautiful condition. Hallmarked London '
  '1795. The epergne was introduced by English silversmiths during the mid-18th century and the '
  'word epergne is a derivative of the French épargne , meaning "a savings." Quite an appropriate '
