  'working condition. Named after the hero of the Battle of Manila Bay during the '
  'Spainish-American War, Admiral George Dewey, these immensely popular machines were copied by '
  'virtually every other slot machine manufacturer of the period, though none ever surpassed the '
  'success of this original model. Designed with a fully exposed, colorful wheel and an '
  'easy-to-operate handle, the Dewey became the model for future generations of slot machines. Its '
  "decorative quality was intended to enhance the interiors of America's finest gambling halls at "
