  'fourteen dining chairs specially made for Mary Todd Lincoln around 1860, the same year that her '
  'husband, Abraham Lincoln, was elected president of the United States. Used in the White House '
  "dining room during President Lincoln's administration, they represent an amazing artifact from "
  'his remarkable legacy. Highly personal artifacts from past presidents are endowed with an '
